    "details": "Ar-Rafi means 'The Exalter' or 'The Elevator'. It signifies that Allah is the One who raises and honors whom He wills. He elevates the status of His servants, raises the righteous in rank, and lifts the humble. He exalts His prophets, saints, and believers. This name complements Al-Khaafid (The Abaser), showing that both exaltation and abasement come from Allah alone.\n\n**Quran References:** 'He will raise you to a station of praise' (17:79). 'And Allah will raise those who have believed among you and those who were given knowledge, by degrees' (58:11).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Ar-Rafi reminds us that true elevation comes from Allah. It encourages us to seek honor through obedience to Him rather than through worldly means.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Ar-Rafi brings honor and respect, elevates one's status in the sight of Allah and people, and helps in achieving noble goals. It is beneficial for those seeking to rise above difficulties.",
