    "details": "Al-Muzil means 'The Humiliator' or 'The Abaser'. It signifies that Allah is the One who humiliates and degrades whom He wills. He brings down the arrogant, exposes the hypocrites, and humbles the oppressors. This is an aspect of His perfect justice. No one can resist His will, and those He humiliates find no one to honor them.\n\n**Quran References:** 'And whoever Allah humiliates, there is no one who can honor him' (22:18). 'You honor whom You will and humble whom You will' (3:26).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Muzil warns against arrogance, oppression, and transgression. It reminds us that humiliation comes from Allah as a consequence of sin and pride.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Muzil protects from arrogance and its consequences. It instills fear of Allah's punishment and encourages humility. It is beneficial for those seeking to overcome their ego and pride.",
