    "meaning": "The Wise, The Judge of Judges, The One who is correct in His doings.",
    "details": "Al-Hakeem means 'The All-Wise' or 'The Perfectly Wise'. It signifies that Allah is the One who possesses absolute wisdom in all His actions, decrees, and commands. His wisdom is perfect and encompasses everything. He creates with wisdom, legislates with wisdom, and decrees with wisdom. Every act of Allah has a purpose and is placed in its proper place with perfect justice and knowledge.\n\n**Quran References:** 'He is the All-Wise (Al-Hakeem), the All-Knowing' (6:18). 'Indeed, Allah is Exalted in Might and Wise' (2:129).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Hakeem teaches us to trust in Allah's wisdom, even when we don't understand His decrees. It encourages us to seek wisdom.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Hakeem increases wisdom, brings understanding, and helps in making sound decisions. It is beneficial for those seeking guidance and clarity.",
