    "details": "Al-Ba'ith means 'The Resurrector' or 'The Awakener'. It signifies that Allah is the One who will resurrect all creatures after death for judgment. He raises the dead from their graves, awakens them from their slumber, and brings them to account. He also sends messengers to awaken humanity from the sleep of heedlessness.\n\n**Quran References:** 'Indeed, Allah is the Resurrector (Al-Ba'ith) of those in the graves' (22:7). 'And We will surely resurrect those who have died' (36:52).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Ba'ith reminds us of the Day of Resurrection and accountability. It encourages preparation for the Hereafter.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Ba'ith increases awareness of the Hereafter, awakens the heart from heedlessness, and encourages good deeds. It is beneficial for those seeking to live with purpose and accountability.",
