    "details": "Ash-Shaheed means 'The Witness' or 'The Testifier'. It signifies that Allah is the One who witnesses all things, nothing escapes His knowledge. He is present and aware of every event, every action, and every word. He is the ultimate witness to all that occurs in the universe, and His testimony is the most truthful. He will testify for or against His servants on the Day of Judgment.\n\n**Quran References:** 'And Allah is Witness (Ash-Shaheed) over all things' (4:33). 'Indeed, Allah is ever Witness over everything' (22:17).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Ash-Shaheed reminds us that Allah witnesses all our actions. This awareness encourages righteousness and sincerity.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Ash-Shaheed increases consciousness of Allah's presence, protects from hypocrisy, and encourages truthfulness. It is beneficial for those seeking to live with integrity and sincerity.",
