    "details": "Al-Haqq means 'The Truth' or 'The Reality'. It signifies that Allah is the ultimate truth, the only true reality, and the One whose existence is absolute and undeniable. Everything else derives its existence from Him. His words are truth, His promises are truth, and His religion is truth. He is the One whose existence is necessary, eternal, and unchanging.\n\n**Quran References:** 'That is because Allah is the Truth (Al-Haqq), and what they call upon besides Him is falsehood' (31:30). 'And the word of your Lord has been fulfilled in truth and justice' (6:115).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Haqq reminds us to seek truth, speak truth, and align our lives with the ultimate reality. It encourages sincerity and honesty.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Haqq brings truthfulness, protects from falsehood, and helps one discern truth from falsehood. It is beneficial for those seeking clarity and guidance.",
