    "details": "Al-Qawwiyy means 'The All-Strong' or 'The Possessor of Perfect Strength'. It signifies that Allah possesses absolute, perfect, and unlimited strength. His power is never diminished, His might never weakens, and His strength is incomparable. He is the One who supports His servants with His strength and empowers whom He wills.\n\n**Quran References:** 'Indeed, Allah is the All-Strong (Al-Qawwiyy), the Almighty' (22:40). 'And it is He who created the heavens and the earth in six days, and His Throne had been upon water' (11:7).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Qawwiyy reminds us that all strength comes from Allah. It encourages us to rely on His strength rather than our own.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Qawwiyy brings strength, protects from weakness, and empowers one to overcome difficulties. It is beneficial for those facing challenges or seeking physical and spiritual strength.",
