    "details": "Al-Mateen means 'The Firm' or 'The Unshakable'. It signifies that Allah's power and strength are constant, unwavering, and never diminish. He is never tired, never weak, and His strength is absolute. His firmness is perfect, and His support is unshakeable. He is the One whose power is continuous and uninterrupted.\n\n**Quran References:** 'Indeed, Allah is the Provider, the Possessor of Strength, the Firm (Al-Mateen)' (51:58). 'And rely upon the Ever-Living who does not die' (25:58).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Mateen reminds us that Allah's power is constant and reliable. It encourages us to rely on His unshakeable strength.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Mateen brings stability, protects from instability, and provides firmness in faith. It is beneficial for those seeking steadfastness and resilience.",
