    "details": "Al-Waliyy means 'The Protecting Friend' or 'The Ally'. It signifies that Allah is the One who protects, supports, and guides His believing servants. He is the close friend and guardian of the righteous, helping them, defending them, and drawing them close to Him. His friendship is the ultimate honor and security.\n\n**Quran References:** 'Allah is the Protector (Al-Waliyy) of those who believe' (2:257). 'He is your Protector, the best of protectors' (22:78).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Waliyy reminds us that Allah is our closest friend and protector. It encourages us to seek His friendship and support.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Waliyy brings divine protection, strengthens one's connection with Allah, and provides support in difficult times. It is beneficial for those seeking closeness to Allah.",
