    "details": "Al-Hameed means 'The Praiseworthy' or 'The All-Lauded'. It signifies that Allah is the One who is worthy of all praise, in all circumstances, and from all creation. His praise is inherent in His perfection, and He is praised for His beauty, His mercy, His justice, and all His attributes. All praise ultimately returns to Him.\n\n**Quran References:** 'He is the Praiseworthy (Al-Hameed), the All-Glorious' (34:6). 'Indeed, Allah is the Self-Sufficient, the Praiseworthy' (31:12).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Hameed reminds us to praise Allah in all situations. It encourages gratitude and glorification.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Hameed brings blessings, increases gratitude, and cultivates a praising heart. It is beneficial for those seeking to develop a thankful disposition.",
