    "details": "Al-Muhsee means 'The Reckoner' or 'The Counter'. It signifies that Allah has perfect knowledge and count of all things. He has counted every atom, every thought, every deed, and every moment. Nothing is forgotten, and nothing is missed. His knowledge encompasses the smallest details and the greatest events.\n\n**Quran References:** 'And We have enumerated all things in a clear register' (36:12). 'And He has counted everything, numbered it completely' (19:94).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Muhsee reminds us that Allah records all our deeds. This encourages accountability and mindfulness of our actions.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Muhsee brings awareness of accountability, protects from negligence, and helps in organizing one's affairs. It is beneficial for those seeking to be more mindful.",
