    "details": "Al-Waali means 'The Protecting Governor' or 'The Master'. It signifies that Allah is the One who has full authority over all creation. He manages the affairs of the universe, protects His righteous servants, and governs with perfect wisdom and justice. He is the patron, the protector, and the sovereign over everything.\n\n**Quran References:** 'Allah is the Protector (Al-Waali) of those who have believed' (2:257). 'And He is the Guardian over all things' (6:102).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Waali gives comfort to believers, knowing that Allah is their protector and governor. He manages their affairs and protects them.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Waali brings protection, security, and assurance that Allah is managing one's affairs. It is beneficial for those seeking protection and guidance.",
