    "transliteration": "At-Tawwaab",
    "translated": "The Ever-Acceptor of Repentance",
    "meaning": "The Relenting, The One who grants repentance to whoever He willed among His creatures and accepts his repentance.",
    "details": "At-Tawwaab means 'The Acceptor of Repentance' or 'The Oft-Returning'. It signifies that Allah constantly accepts the repentance of His servants, no matter how many times they sin and return to Him. He turns to them with mercy and forgives them. He loves those who repent and encourages them to seek His forgiveness repeatedly.\n\n**Quran References:** 'Indeed, He is the Acceptor of Repentance (At-Tawwaab), the Merciful' (2:37). 'And turn to Allah in repentance, all of you, O believers, that you might succeed' (24:31).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** At-Tawwaab gives immense hope to sinners. No matter how many times we fall, Allah is always ready to accept our repentance.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting At-Tawwaab encourages repentance, brings hope in Allah's mercy, and helps in overcoming sins. It is beneficial for those struggling with repeated mistakes.",
