    "details": "Ar-Ra'oof means 'The Compassionate' or 'The Kind'. It signifies that Allah has extreme mercy, tenderness, and compassion towards His servants. His compassion is deeper than that of a mother for her child. He is gentle with His creation, overlooks their faults, and treats them with kindness even when they err.\n\n**Quran References:** 'Indeed, Allah is Kind (Ar-Ra'oof) and Merciful to the people' (2:143). 'And He is the Kind, the Merciful' (9:117).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Ar-Ra'oof reminds us of Allah's gentle mercy. It encourages us to be compassionate towards others.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Ar-Ra'oof brings Allah's special mercy, increases compassion, and softens the heart. It is beneficial for those seeking gentleness and kindness.",
