    "meaning": "The Equitable, The One who is Just in His judgment.",
    "details": "Al-Muqsit means 'The Equitable' or 'The Just'. It signifies that Allah is the One who establishes justice and fairness in all matters. He judges with perfect equity, neither oppressing nor favoring anyone. He gives everyone their due rights and ensures that justice prevails. His justice is absolute, and He loves those who act justly.\n\n**Quran References:** 'And Allah is the Just (Al-Muqsit); there is no deity except Him' (3:18). 'Indeed, Allah loves those who act justly' (5:42).\n\n**Spiritual Significance:** Al-Muqsit reminds us of Allah's perfect justice. It encourages us to be just in our dealings with others.\n\n**Benefit:** Reciting Al-Muqsit brings justice in one's affairs, protects from oppression, and helps in making fair decisions. It is beneficial for those seeking justice or dealing with disputes.",
